$ Excel: Developer -> Controls -> Design Mode

The sole purpose of *Developer -> Controls -> Design Mode* is to turn Design Mode on or off.

Design mode must be turned on in order to group, copy, resize or format *controls* on a â†’ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet.

Design Mode might be *greyed out*. In that case, it can be enabled by clicking Developer->Controls->View-Code[View Code]
